    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/4–352</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum for the Record, by the Deputy Assistant Secretary
                        of State for Far Eastern Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-03">April 3,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Meeting with <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>, April 3, 1952</item>
                </list>
                <p>A meeting was held between State and the <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> at
                    3:45 p.m., April 3, to discuss the reply to <persName corresp="#p_RGMB1">General
                        Ridgway</persName>’s HNC 1118<note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d81">Supra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> which had been received the same afternoon. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_AJM1">Allison</persName>, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NPH1"
                        >Nitze</persName>, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SCC1">Stelle</persName> and Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> were present for State, and
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGOTAON1">General Bradley</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGJL1">General Collins</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_VGHS1"
                        >General Vandenberg</persName> and Admiral <persName>Duncan</persName> for
                    the <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>.</p>
                <p>There was immediate and general agreement that <persName corresp="#p_RGMB1"
                        >General Ridgway</persName> should immediately be authorized to undertake
                    the action proposed in Part 1 of his HNC 1118. There was also general agreement
                    that he should be authorized to take the action proposed in Part 2 of HNC 1118,
                    but that the advantages of proposing the Soviet Union as a member of the
                    supervisory commission not designated as “neutral” should be more fully set
                    forth to him. Accordingly a draft telegram along these lines replying to Part 2
                    was discussed and agreed to.</p>
                <p>The drafts of the telegrams were subsequently discussed with the Secretary, and
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGOTAON1">General Bradley</persName> was informed of
                    the Department’s concurrence the same afternoon. <persName corresp="#p_BGOTAON1"
                        >General Bradley</persName> undertook to obtain the <pb facs="0173" n="139"
                        xml:id="pg_139"/> President’s approval and the telegrams (<gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 905426<note n="2" xml:id="d81fn2">Not printed;
                        it approved action proposed in HNC 1118, part 1 and informed <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> that the decision on part 2 was
                        being sent by a separate message, <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 905427
                        to <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>, Apr. 3.
                        (795.00/4–352)</note> and <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 905427)<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d81fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d82">Infra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> were dispatched the evening of the same day.</p>
            </div>
